  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the lamb shoulder and cook for 2 minutes on each side.",
    "Remove the lamb from the skillet and set aside.",
    "Add the onions, garlic, and red bell pepper to the skillet and cook until the vegetables are tender, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the soaked dried red chillies, tomatoes, salt, black pepper, paprika, cardamom, cumin, coriander, turmeric, cayenne pepper, and garam masala to the skillet and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.",
    "Return the lamb to the skillet and cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.",
    "Stir in the yogurt, cilantro, and lemon juice.",
    "Cook for an additional 2 minutes, until the sauce has thickened.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with additional cilantro if desired.",
    "Adjust the seasoning as needed, adding more chilli powder if desired for extra heat.",
    "Serve over rice or with naan bread for a delicious meal."
